<a name="3477"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Put Your Thinking Cap On</div>
<br />
Knowing the latest trends in consumer electronics is among the best ways to succeed in this ever-changing industry. CES is the place to learn from the pros. Training, trends, tutorials and hundreds of hard-hitting, down-and-dirty panels get to the core of what’s happening in high-tech. See our favorite five session picks this week.<BR><BR>Here are five sessions to consider:<BR><BR><IMG hspace=5 align=right src="/print/images/content/icce_10.08.jpg" width=75 height=81><A href="http://cesweb.org/sessions/search/results.asp?categoryID=1846">International Conference on Consumer Electronics (ICCE)</A> <BR>The ICCE, organized by the IEEE Consumer Electronics Society, is your opportunity to review the latest research and development ideas and to learn about the next generation of CE products. Join us for four informative keynotes, four technology tutorials and myriad technical presentations from experts at top companies.<BR><BR><IMG hspace=5 align=left src="/print/images/content/JEDEC.gif" width=161 height=41><A href="http://cesweb.org/sessions/search/results.asp?categoryID=1877">Storage Solutions: Flash Memory in Consumer Products</A><BR>Flash Memory technology is the predominant storage medium in consumer electronics. It offers low-cost, high-performing, reliable storage solutions for countless consumer devices and computing products, from Smartphones to digital cameras to netbooks. Discover how technological advancements and upcoming standards for flash cards and solid state drives will impact future devices.<BR><BR><IMG hspace=5 align=right src="/print/images/content/CES-431_MPEG_Industry-Forum.jpg" width=180 height=60><A href="http://cesweb.org/sessions/search/results.asp?categoryID=1876">MPEGIF Master Class: TV X.0 - Present & Future</A> <BR>The MPEGIF Master Classes formerly held at NAB and IBC are now at CES 2010. This event features senior executives and experts with a wealth of knowledge about digital media and television. Join us as they discuss their experiences in developing, deploying and monetizing new video services. Speakers will provide unique insights into progress with the latest technology, new business models and regulatory issues facing next generation digital video entertainment.<BR><BR><IMG hspace=5 align=left src="/print/images/content/StorageVisions_web.gif" width=125 height=104><A href="http://cesweb.org/sessions/search/results.asp?categoryID=1859">Storage Visions® 2010</A><BR>The Storage Visions® Partner Program convenes technologists, vendors, entrepreneurs, analysts and users to determine how to turn bytes into bucks. Digital storage drives recovery by allowing consumers to create more immersive content and to preserve, protect and search their lives. Conference sessions examine the infrastructure supporting the growth of richer media experiences, including storage technologies; privacy protection; metadata generation and indexing technologies; remote, home and mobile storage; next generation user needs; and business opportunities.<BR><BR><A href="http://cesweb.org/sessions/search/results.asp?categoryID=1837">Emerging Technology Knowledge Track<BR></A>New technologies emerge at the speed of light, but are they all buzzworthy? Market-makers? Consumer must-haves? Or are they soon to be yesterday's news? These entertaining sessions evaluate what's in and what's out across many categories of emerging technology. <BR><BR><A href="/print/sessions/default.asp">View the complete conference session lineup.</A><BR>

